  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Playing (Soccer) For Change in Nicaragua</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We use soccer, the world&apos;s most popular team sport, as a vehicle for positive change in the lives of girls ages 5-20 in Granada, Nicaragua. A team can be the most powerful change agent in a young girl&apos;s development, proven to inspire healthy choices regarding drugs, sex, alcohol, academics, and nutrition.  Through a combination of on and off-field activities, including school scholarships and tutoring, the program creates pathways to uncommon outcomes for the girls of Granada.</narrative>
  </description>
